laboratory_examinations.findings: There is a 3.4 x 1.6 cm fluid collection surrounding the appendix posterior to the cecum (previously 2.9 x 3.9 cm on CT). Edematous appearance of the cecum is most likely secondary to local inflammatory changes.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Fluid collection size increased from 2.9 x 3.9 cm on CT to 3.4 x 1.6 cm on ultrasound.
